8. Active path: Dashboard Quality Section G
Current function name
runFrameworkTest6DateFormattingCore_
Production role
Despite the legacy “Framework Test 6” name, this currently acts as:

Dashboard Quality Section G — Date Format Integrity
The A–G validation path calls it directly for Section G. 

Active path
runFrameworkTest6DateFormattingCore_
  -> activeDashboard = dashboard || loadDashboardConfig_()
  -> results = []
  -> for each dashboard.sheetDefinition:
       testDateFormattingForTemplate_(activeDashboard, sheetDef)
       append results
       mark "Checked date formats: template"
  -> writeFrameworkTest6DateFormatReport_(results, options)
  -> mark "Dashboard Quality Section G staged" if deferred
     OR "Dashboard Quality Section G saved" if direct
  -> return results
The Section G runner loops all sheet definitions and writes/stages the date-format report. 

Per-template Section G check
testDateFormattingForTemplate_
Active path
testDateFormattingForTemplate_
  -> get template sheet by sheetDef.templateName
  -> get globals
  -> get headers for sheet type

  If sheet missing:
    -> return FAIL result

  Build dateChecks:
    -> for each header:
       -> dashboard.columnDefinitions[header]
       -> if def.dateColumn:
            expectedFormat = getExpectedNumberFormat_
            expectedSheetsFormat = getGoogleSheetsNumberFormat_
            push date check

  If no dateChecks:
    -> return empty results

  Read sample number formats:
    -> sampleRows = min(10, maxRows from dataStart)
    -> lastCol = headers.length
    -> getRange(dataStartRow, 1, sampleRows, lastCol).getNumberFormats()

  For each date check:
    -> collect unique actual formats
    -> compare to expected format
    -> if failed and repair enabled:
         repairDateFormatForSectionG_
         reread repaired sample column
    -> push PASS/FAIL result
