These are not removal instructions yet — just active-path observations.

13.1 Section G is production-active but legacy-named
Current active production path:

runDashboardQualityTemplateAndFormatSections_
  -> runFrameworkTest6DateFormattingCore_
This means a function named as a framework test is actively responsible for Dashboard Quality Section G. 

Recommended future cleanup:

runDashboardQualitySectionGDateFormatIntegrity_
with a temporary wrapper:

runFrameworkTest6DateFormattingCore_
  -> runDashboardQualitySectionGDateFormatIntegrity_
13.2 Section G storage key is still test-named
Section G uses:

RFF_TEST6_DATE_FORMAT_SHEET
The constant currently points to:

"Framework Test 6 Date Format Report"
That constant is defined here. 

This is active in the F–G path when reading/writing Section G rows. 

Recommended future cleanup:

RFF_DASHBOARD_QUALITY_SECTION_G_DATE_FORMAT_KEY
with the old key retained temporarily if needed for migration.

13.3 Section G currently can repair while validating
Section G checks formats and, if repair is enabled, calls repair logic during validation. 

The repair function formats the full data column range. 

Recommended future cleanup:

audit function separate from repair function
13.4 Dashboard Quality writer is active and performance-sensitive
F–G batch write goes through replaceDashboardQualitySectionsRows_, which can perform section row replacement and style updated sections. 

The single-section writer can insert/delete rows, clear content, and write values. 

Recommended future cleanup:

fast path when section size unchanged
more granular timing inside section writer
avoid unnecessary style passes
